# 📌 Executive Summary

On 25 February 2026, LogN Pacific Financial Services experienced a Business Email Compromise (BEC) attack resulting in a fraudulent wire transfer attempt of £24,500. The transaction was flagged and frozen by the receiving bank.

Investigation revealed that the attacker gained access to a finance employee’s account (Mark Smith) using an MFA fatigue (push bombing) attack. The attacker then established persistence via inbox rules, conducted email reconnaissance, and sent a fraudulent invoice email to another internal employee.

The attacker also accessed cloud storage services including OneDrive and SharePoint, expanding the potential impact to include data exposure.

The activity aligns with known TTPs of the threat group **Scattered Spider**.

