# 🧠 Lessons Learned

* MFA alone is not sufficient — users can be socially engineered into approving malicious requests
* Conditional Access policies must be enforced to block risky sign-ins from unmanaged devices and locations
* Inbox rule monitoring is critical for detecting stealthy persistence in BEC attacks
* Internal emails (IntraOrg) bypass traditional email security controls
* Session-based correlation provides high-confidence attribution across cloud activity
* Cloud environments require unified visibility across identity, email, and storage logs

